(% style=&amp;#34;color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial sans-serif; font-size: 0.6em&amp;#34; %)Designing for energy as material and symbolic  Proposing a more explicit treatment of the design of energy  as both material…is merely “something to”—  something undemanding and undeserving of our sustained  care and attention.

(% style=&amp;#34;margin-bottom: 0in; &amp;#34; %)
